e]; female). Scale bar = 5 mm." captionText-3="FIG. 7. Rami of V.melissa, USNM 548310 (A) and V. elisabethae, sp. nov., USNM 319284 (B). Note spiculelike m3 in V. melissa (lacking in V. elisabethae) and posterolabial cusp on p4 in V. elisabethae (lacking in V. melissa). Scale bar = 5 mm." captionText-4="FIG. 8. Partial views of the basicranial region of V. melissa, USNM 548310 (A); V. sinchi, sp. nov., FMNH 114028 [holotype] (B); V. elisabethae, sp. nov., USNM 319282 (C). Abbreviations: be, bony excrescence; cb, extension of caudal border of pterygoid; fo, foramen ovale; pg, postglenoid process; sf, orbitosphenoid fissure. Scale bar = 5 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367605" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367607" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367609" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367613" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367615" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5367605/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5367607/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5367609/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/5367613/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/5367615/files/figure.png" pageId="8">Figures 4–8</figureCitation>
